It was a sense of how can we actually translate that data structure into the one that the

00:20:02.239 --> 00:20:07.280
model was actually going to represent that represents this particular modeling task.

00:20:07.280 --> 00:20:10.880
But that is actually a really good question, because as I'm sure if you've worked with

00:20:10.880 --> 00:20:17.479
LSTMs and these kinds of models, they can accommodate various lengths, right?

00:20:17.479 --> 00:20:23.239
So you could potentially say given the player's entire history, given a player that has played

00:20:23.239 --> 00:20:27.119
whether they played two years or ten years or however long they played, what is their

